main event: Multiple sightings of unidentified flying objects were reported from the Niagara Falls area on June 13, 1963.
interesting points: Witnesses reported the sightings to the Air Force through representatives of the press.
The sightings were investigated by the USAF Project Information Office.
The objects were determined to not be a balloon, aircraft, satellite, or meteor.
The objects were likely a satellite returning to Jupiter, which left a long afterglow.
The sightings lasted for approximately 40 minutes.
witnesses: multiple witnesses, including representatives of the press and Air Force personnel
photographs: no photographs present in the report
